The <code><strong>ImageBitmap</strong></code> interface represents a bitmap image which can be drawn to a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/canvas" title="Use the HTML &lt;canvas&gt; element with either the canvas scripting API or the WebGL API to draw graphics and animations."><code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code></a> without undue latency. It can be created from a variety of source objects using the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageBitmapFactories/createImageBitmap" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>createImageBitmap()</code></a> factory method. <code>ImageBitmap</code> provides an asynchronous and resource efficient pathway to prepare textures for rendering in WebGL.